{"title":"Bianchi Impulso RC is a Lightweight, Aero Gravel Race Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-impulso-rc-is-a-lightweight-aero-gravel-race-bike/","date":1700670469000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1488\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso rc\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1-297x221.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1-800x595.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1-120x89.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1-768x571.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-1-1536x1143.jpg 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Applying their top-level Reparto Course treatment to the gravel segment, the new Bianchi Impulso RC brings aerodynamic shaping and lightweight layups to the dirt track.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Recently overhauled <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-oltre-rc-hyperbike-gets-air-deflectors-and-vented-integrated-stem/\">Oltre RC</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-specialissima-all-around-road-bike/\">Specialissima RC</a> road bikes inspired this race version of the Impulso gravel bike, and a lot of similarities unite the bikes aesthetically. The Impulso RC starts off with a fully integrated stealth front end, no hoses to be seen.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso rc angle view of cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Back on the bike, the fork’s crown shape is integrated into the downtube, which is shaped to move air smoothly across the frame. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso rc side view of downtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-6-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not convinced this is made only for racing? The max 700×42 tire clearance should do the trick. Those are fitted to Bianchi’s RC43 aero wheels (25mm internal width, 43mm deep, 1,530g).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1383\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso rc front view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2-297x205.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2-800x553.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2-120x83.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2-768x531.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-2-1536x1062.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The geometry is inspired by XC mountain bikes with a (slightly) shorter stem than their road bikes, but with longer reach. The BB drop is a healthy 70mm, keeping the rider low in the bike for sharper handling.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The seatstays bow slightly to allow a bit of compliance, which is good because you won’t get much from the aero-shaped seatpost.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1820\" height=\"1349\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2024 bianchi impulso rc frame and cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8.jpg 1820w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8-297x220.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8-800x593.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8-120x89.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8-768x569.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-RC-aero-gravel-bike-8-1536x1138.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The handlebar is narrow-ish at the hoods to keep the rider in a streamlined, narrow position, but not as extreme as some competitors. They range from 40-44cm at the hoods. The one-piece bar/stem combo flare out 16º for more leverage in the drops, too. Claimed weight is just 340g, stem lengths from 90-120mm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The top RC model comes in at a claimed 8.1kg (17.83lb) and runs €5,578.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1588\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso pro\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4-297x236.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4-800x635.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4-120x95.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4-768x610.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Pro-aero-gravel-bike-4-1536x1220.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Below that is the Impulso Pro, which switches to a standard stem and handlebar, lower level carbon fiber, and a Velomann Terbium wheelset. MSRP is €3,463, claimed weight is 8.9kg (19.65lb).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1586\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"2024 bianchi impulso comp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3-297x236.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3-800x634.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3-120x95.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3-768x609.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-bianchi-impulso-Comp-aero-gravel-bike-3-1536x1218.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Comp model gets Fulcrum wheels and Velomann alloy bar and stem. MSRP is €2,459, no weight listed. All models use full internal routing and are compatible with 1x and 2x drivetrains, including mechanical groups. Both the Pro and Comp models are also available in Bianchi’s signature Celeste color, too. All prices excluding VAT.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bianchi</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bianchi-impulso-rc-is-a-lightweight-aero-gravel-race-bike/\">Bianchi Impulso RC is a Lightweight, Aero Gravel Race Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"126b4bdb4846e483ca239f341b2a64c8ece22a6e81de03f8313141447b269110","category":"Cycling"}